rComments: I took this class as a GE and have never taken an art history class before and had zero prior knowledge about anything. Lecture is excellent and was easy for me to follow. Essays are easy and don't take that long. Exams are easy if you memorize the pictures posted online. Easy/enjoyable class for a GE don't stress about it.

Class itself is very interesting and has great potential, the teacher just makes it so boring. Not sure if it is just her being nervous but she always says "uh and um" and it makes it irritating and very hard to pay attention. I would definitely take another art history class just not with her.

Elizabeth Aguilera is one of the most passionate professors I have had at this university. She explains everything clearly and teaches at a great pace. Did not really have a interest in the class but she made everything in the class interesting and at times funny.

I took this class as a GE, having never previously taking an Art History course. Elizabeth makes the topic very interesting to learn and I ended up greatly enjoying the class. If I could take another class from her I definitely would!
